Exactly at that time Asharaf Barati, a 13-year-old boy who belongs to the ethnic group of Hazara, in the province of Ghazni in central Afghani for the last time with his family at dinner together.
Even if his mother never said it at that time, she knew she would not see her son very long, maybe even more.
During the morning of dawn, the boy should break.
