Approximately 20,000 Afghans live in Italy according to official estimates.
For many of them, the country is a transition solution to other European countries.
In recent years, some Afghan-driven companies, including cutting eries, travel agencies, hotels and restaurants.
Some Afghan restaurants even praised in the Italian media for their excellent cuisine.
