"where a risk is, there are also possibilities," says Asharaf with a smile. "I want to invest in Afghanistan.
I never forget my country and I cannot live happily if I know that my people suffer.
I plan a project for farmers from the poorest provinces of the country, especially for women.
They represent half of society and must have the same possibilities as everyone else. "
Ashark forged plans for the opening of a factory in Kabul in which people can learn packaging and preserving techniques. "thus, they can sell their appointments on the market and improve their financial situation," he says.
The development of successful entrepreneur was a journey through uncertainty and doubt, but at the end there are stability and prosperity.
Ashark has made this journey itself. now he wants to help other Afghans on this way.
